{"title_page": "J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox football tournament\n|name                =J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship\n|logo                =\n|caption             =\n|founded             ={{Start date and age|2008}}\n|region              =South America ([[CONMEBOL]]) and Japan ([[Japan Football Association|JFA]])\n|number of teams     =2\n|current champions   ={{nowrap|{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Club Athletico Paranaense|Athletico Paranaense]] (1st title)}} \n|most successful club={{nowrap|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Kashima Antlers]] (2 titles)}} \n|broadcasters        = [[Fox Sports (Latin America)]] (until 2018)<br>[[DirecTV|DirecTV Sports]] (South America) (from 2019)<br>[[ESPN Brasil]] (from 2019)<br>[[Fuji TV]] (Japan)\n|current             = [[2019 J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship]]\n}}\n\nThe '''J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship''' is an annual intercontinental [[association football|football]] match held in [[Japan]], contested by the reigning champions of the [[J.League Cup]] and the [[Copa Sudamericana]].\n\nThe tournament was previously officially called the ''Suruga Bank Championship'' between 2008 and 2018 as it was sponsored by Suruga Bank. Since 2019, it is officially called the ''J. League YBC Levain Cup / CONMEBOL Sudamericana Championship Final'', using the official names of the two qualifying tournaments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/match/j_conmebol_2019/|title=J.LEAGUE YBC LEVAIN CUP / CONMEBOL SUDAMERICANA Championship Final|publisher=Japan Football Association}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship was established in early 2008 by the [[Japan Football Association]] (JFA), [[CONMEBOL]], and [[J. League]], and sponsored by Suruga Bank in Japan. The championship is hosted annually at the [[J. League Cup]] champion's home stadium.\n\nThe first match was played on July 30, 2008 at [[Nagai Stadium]] in [[Osaka]] where Argentina's [[Arsenal de Sarand\u00ed|Arsenal]] defeated Japan's [[Gamba Osaka]] by 1\u20130.\n\n==Finals==\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" width=100%\n!Season\n!Country\n!Winner\n!Score\n!Runner-up\n!Country\n!Venue\n!Attendance\n|-\n|align=center|[[2008 Suruga Bank Championship|2008]]\n|{{flag|ARG}}\n|[[Arsenal de Sarand\u00ed|Arsenal]]\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|[[Gamba Osaka]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Nagai Stadium]], [[Osaka]]\n|align=center|19,728\n|-\n|align=center|[[2009 Suruga Bank Championship|2009]]\n|{{flag|BRA}}\n|[[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]]\n|align=center|2\u20131\n|[[Oita Trinita]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[\u014cita Stadium]], [[\u014cita, \u014cita|\u014cita]]\n|align=center|16,505\n|-\n|align=center|[[2010 Suruga Bank Championship|2010]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[FC Tokyo]]\n|align=center|2\u20132 (4\u20133 [[penalty shootout (association football)|pen.]])\n|[[Liga Deportiva Universitaria de Quito|LDU Quito]]\n|{{flag|ECU}}\n|[[Olympic Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]], [[Tokyo]]\n|align=center|19,423\n|-\n|align=center|[[2011 Suruga Bank Championship|2011]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]\n|align=center|2\u20132 (4\u20132 [[penalty shootout (association football)|pen.]])\n|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico Independiente|Independiente]]\n|{{flag|ARG}}\n|[[Shizuoka Stadium]], [[Fukuroi, Shizuoka|Fukuroi]]\n|align=center|19,034\n|-\n|align=center|[[2012 Suruga Bank Championship|2012]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Kashima Antlers]]\n|align=center|2\u20132 (7\u20136 [[penalty shootout (association football)|pen.]])\n|[[Club Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]]\n|{{flag|CHI}}\n|[[Kashima Soccer Stadium]], [[Kashima, Ibaraki|Kashima]]\n|align=center|20,021\n|-\n|align=center|[[2013 Suruga Bank Championship|2013]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Kashima Antlers]]\n|align=center|3\u20132\n|[[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n|{{flag|BRA}}\n|[[Kashima Soccer Stadium]], [[Kashima, Ibaraki|Kashima]]\n|align=center|26,695\n|-\n|align=center|[[2014 Suruga Bank Championship|2014]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Kashiwa Reysol]]\n|align=center|2\u20131\n|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico Lan\u00fas |Lan\u00fas]]\n|{{flag|ARG}}\n|[[Hitachi Kashiwa Stadium]], [[Kashiwa]]\n|align=center|10,140\n|-\n|align=center|[[2015 Suruga Bank Championship|2015]]\n|{{flag|ARG}}\n|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]\n|align=center|3\u20130\n|[[Gamba Osaka]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Osaka Expo '70 Stadium]], [[Osaka]]\n|align=center|12,722\n|-\n|align=center|[[2016 Suruga Bank Championship|2016]]\n|{{flag|COL}}\n|[[Independiente Santa Fe|Santa Fe]]\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|[[Kashima Antlers]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Kashima Soccer Stadium]], [[Kashima, Ibaraki|Kashima]]\n|align=center|19,716\n|-\n|align=center|[[2017 Suruga Bank Championship|2017]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Urawa Red Diamonds]]\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|[[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Chapecoense de Futebol|Chapecoense]]\n|{{flag|BRA}}\n|[[Saitama Stadium 2002]], [[Saitama, Saitama|Saitama]]\n|align=center|11,002\n|-\n|align=center|[[2018 Suruga Bank Championship|2018]]\n|{{flag|ARG}}\n|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico Independiente|Independiente]]\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|[[Cerezo Osaka]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Yanmar Stadium Nagai]], [[Osaka]]\n|align=center|10,035\n|-\n|align=center|[[2019 J.League Cup / Copa Sudamericana Championship|2019]]\n|{{flag|BRA}}\n|[[Club Athletico Paranaense|Athletico Paranaense]]\n|align=center|4\u20130\n|[[Shonan Bellmare]]\n|{{flag|JPN}}\n|[[Shonan BMW Stadium Hiratsuka|Shonan BMW Stadium]], [[Hiratsuka]]\n|align=center|9,129\n|-id=\"2020\"\n|align=center|2020\n|colspan=7 align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"ZZZ\"|Not held due to [[2020 Summer Olympics]] held at the same time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jfa.jp/match/news/00023243/|title=\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0YBC\u30eb\u30f4\u30a1\u30f3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7/CONMEBOL\u30b9\u30c0\u30e1\u30ea\u30ab\u30fc\u30ca \u738b\u8005\u6c7a\u5b9a\u6226\u306e2020\u5e74\u958b\u50ac\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=[[Japan Football Association]]|date=26 October 2019|language=Japanese|trans-title=About th